Nicholas Cox has lived in Stanstead St Margarets for twenty years and sits on the Parish Council.
Nick was involved in the Hoddesdon incinerator campaign from its inception. He’s a long-standing member of Greenpeace and a life member of the Environmental Investigation Agency (EIA).
He is a leading authority on sustainable refrigeration and air conditioning, and has provided refrigerant environmental impact assessments to blue chip clients, the UK government and EU.
Nick Says:
I care passionately about the local area, I’m a regular walker along the Lea Valley towpath and I’m a keen supporter of live music events in Hoddesdon and Broxbourne. I already work with local pressure groups.
My platform will be based on the following aims of the Green Party:
- taking back our NHS from creeping privatisation;
- creating a fair economy that works for all;
- secure, affordable, decent homes for everyone;
- investing in fossil free affordable energy;
- abolishing tuition fees and investing in quality education; and
- making public transport public.
